  "prob_desc_output_spec": "Print one integer — the minimal possible number of stones that can be in the pile after these $$$n$$$ operations.",
  "source_code": "#include<stdio.h>\nint main()\n{\n    int n;\n    scanf(\"%d\",&n);\n    char ch[n+1];\n    scanf(\"%s\",ch);\n    int cnt=0,nct=0,minus=0,sum=0;\n    for(int i=0;ch[i]!='\\0';i++){\n        if(ch[i]=='+'){\n            sum++;\n        }\n        else if(ch[i]=='-'){\n            sum--;\n        }\n        if(sum<0){\n            sum=0;\n        }\n    }\n    printf(\"%d\\n\",sum);\n    return 0;\n}\n",
